What will console output below? 
let sum = function(a, b) {
    console.log(a + b);
}

console.log(sum(3, 2));


üö®üö®üö® ANSWER BELOW üö®üö®üö®
The code will return the number 5 and undefined. This is because the code didn't explicitly return any value! 
It first logs (a + b), then it calls the function, which will return undefined:
let sum = function(a, b) {
    console.log(a + b);
    //no return;
} 

console.log(sum(3, 2)); //returns 5 and undefined


